(1, '', 'อาจารย์', 'Instructor', 'ดร.', '', 'ภัทรา', 'Pattara', 'Khamrin', 'คำรินทร์', '', 'My research interests are focused on the molecular epidemiology of gastroenteritis viruses (rotavirus, calicivirus, astrovirus, adenovirus, kobuvirus, parechovirus, bocavirus etc.) in humans and animals, and development of rapid detection methods for diarrheal viruses.\r\n', '', 'pattara.k@cmu.ac.th', 'pkhamrin@gmail.com', '0', '', 'uploads/staff/pattra.jpg', 'Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai Univeristy, Chiang Mai, Thailand\r\n\r\nTel: +66-53-935332 ext.429\r\n', '<b>2010  Ph.D. (International Health)</b>, Graduate School of Medicine, The University of Tokyo, Tokyo, Japan</br>\r\n<b>2012 Postdoctoral Fellow</b>, The Japan Society for the Promotion of Sciences (JSPS), Japan\r\n', '2016-10-31 13:22:15', '2016-10-15 15:41:02'),
