(3, '', 'ศาสตราจารย์', 'Professor', 'ดร.', '', 'นิวัตน์', 'Niwat', 'Maneekarn', 'มณีกาญจน์', '', 'Professor Niwat Maneekarn focuses his research area on the molecular epidemiology and characterization of the viruses that cause diarrhea in humans and animals including rotavirus,norovirus,sapovirus, astrovirus, adenovirus, enterovirus, kobuvirus, parechovirus, scaffold virus, cosavirus,etc. The emerging and re-emerging of new variants as well as zoonotic potential of these viruses are also the aspects of his interest. He has published more than 119 papers in the international journals with citation more than 2155 times. His H-index is 30', '', 'niwat.m@cmu.ac.th', 'nmaneeka@gmail.com', '0', '', 'uploads/staff/niwat.jpg', '110 Inthawarorose, T. Sripume, A. Maung, Chiang Mai 50200, THAILAND       \r\nTel: 66-818812460', '<b>1972  D.V.M. (Honors)</b>, Veterinary Medicine, Chulalongkorn University, Bangkok, Thailand   1974   M.Sc. (Pathobiology), Mahidol University, Bangkok, Thailand</br>\r\n<b>1985  Ph.D. (Microbiology and Immunology)</b>, University of Illinois at Chicago, Health Science Center, Chicago, Illinois, USA', '2016-10-31 13:24:26', '2016-10-15 15:50:33'),
(4, '', 'อาจารย์', 'Instructor', 'ดร.', '', 'แคทรียา', 'Kattareeya', 'Kumthip', 'คำทิพย์', '', 'My research focuses on the molecular epidemiology of gastroenteritis viruses in humans and animals including foodborne and waterborne viral pathogens. I am particularly interested in investigation of emerging viruses in animal reservoirs that can be a source of virus for human transmission. ', '', 'kattareeya.k@cmu.ac.th', 'kumthipk@yahoo.com', '0', '', 'uploads/staff/Kattareeya_Kumthip.png', 'Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand\r\nTel: +66-53-935332 ', '<b>2005  B.Sc. (Medical Technology with the first class Honors)</b>, Faculty of Associated Medical Sciences, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai, Thailand </br>\r\n<b>2012  Ph.D. (Microbiology)</b>, Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai, Thailand</br>\r\n<b>2015  Postdoctoral Fellow</b>, Department of Microbiology, Immunology and Biochemistry, University of Tennessee Health Science Center Memphis, Tennessee, U.S.A.', '2016-10-31 13:24:59', '2016-10-15 15:52:00'),
(5, '', 'ผู้ช่วยศาสตราจารย์', 'Assistant Professor', 'ดร.', '', 'มณสิชา', 'Monsicha', 'Pongpom', 'ป้องป้อม', '', 'Study several aspects in biology of pathogenic fungi Talaromyces marneffei and Aspergillus fumigatus, particular interest on their pathogenicity. The main project is characterization of virulence associated genes and genes encoding immunogenic proteins by using molecular biology methods. ', '', 'patthamapp@yahoo.com', '', '0', '', 'uploads/staff/monsicha.jpg', 'Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University\r\nTel: 053-935332', '<b>2004  Ph.D. (Microbiology)</b>, Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai, Thailand  ', '2016-10-31 13:25:24', '2016-10-15 15:52:41'),
