(7, '', 'อาจารย์', 'Instructor', 'ดร.นพ.', '', 'ปารเมศ', 'Parameth', 'Thiennimitr', 'เทียนนิมิตร', '', '1. Molecular pathogenesis of Salmonellosis and uropathogenic E. coli urinary tract infection and their immunomodulations by probiotic, prebiotic and synbiotic.        \r\n2. Host-microbe interactions in some non-communicable diseases such as metabolic syndromes, inflammatory bowel disease                            ', '', 'parameth@gmail.com', 'parameth.t@cmu.ac.th', '0', '', 'uploads/staff/paramet.jpg', '50th year building, Room 718, Department of Microbiology, Faculty of Medicine, Chiang Mai University\r\nTel: 053-935332"\r\n', '<b>1998  B.Sc. (Food Science and technology)(Hons)</b>, Faculty of Agro-Industry, Chiang Mai University, Chiang Mai, Thailand</br>\r\n<b>2004  M.D. (Hons)</b>, Faculty of Medicine, Naresuan University, Phitsanulok, Thailand</br>\r\n<b>2012  Ph.D. (Microbiology)</b>, University of California, Davis, USA</br>\r\n<b>2014 Postdoctoral Fellow (Microbiology & Immunology)</b>, Stanford University School of Medicine, Palo Alto, California, USA\r\n', '2016-10-31 13:26:24', '2016-10-15 15:55:25'),
